{"key":"post-12624946","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12624946</id>\n<content>Don't use a 'frosting layer' of grains on top.&amp;nbsp; That's a long debunked procedure.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition to what myco said, the grains can dry out later, allowing the mycelium on them to weaken, and then trichoderma takes advantage and colonizes the grains.&amp;nbsp; Always cover all grains fully with substrate or casing mix.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12624956</next>\n<prev>12624833</prev>\n<first>12624187</first>\n<last>12626724</last>\n<when>1274799701</when>\n<utime>05/25/10 06:01 PM</utime>\n</post>"}